			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If you can, I suggest going to Rivervale and finding a nice hgh-level caster to bind you there. Most will do this for a small price, and a few will do this for free. I would wait untill you have gotten your level 4 spells, though. The reason to go to Rivervale? The spawns outside it in Misty Thicket can take you up to level 8 and Rivervale is one zone, unlike Qeynos (2) or Freeport(3). Once you have reached level 8 you must travel back to Qeynos and then Erudian to get good prices on spells. In Rivervale the little people for the most part will welcome you into a group because Halflings have non-wisdom casters. This advice works best for Enchanters, because you get Invisability (sp) at level 4. I traveled to Rivervale at level 5 with a level 4 Enchanter, now I am having trouble getting back. I would pay for a guide but I am broke because my guide left me in the middle of West Karana, and I had to pay someone else to help me loot my corpe. My point is its a great place for levels 4-7. Once you hit level 7 you should try to find a way back to Erudian while you are hunting. I didn't and I regret it.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Adaar<BR>
Erudian Wizard of the Eighth Season<BR>
Brell Serills
				</font>
