			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				i started the game as a human mage. figured it was best until i learned the races. well that lasted for a night or 2 until i was creating a new character. was interested in a mage with HIGH INT. in this there is no equal. erudites are the best plain and simple. i checked out a few different options. and decided that a high INT made the difference in spells since magic is the key to any caster its plain to see that mana is the key to any magic. after a few different characters i decided to put every single point into INT with a few cheap rings my INT is a nice 146. at 17lvl that adds up to some serious (you know what). theres nothing like making your own food and drink while the others struggle to find a merchant. and even though my STR is only 60 i found i can still travel with my wieght at a whopping 150. mind you i dont walk fast but if i get tired of dragging i gate to safety. as for memorizing i have found that i mem spells quite fast less than a few seconds for a 16lvl spell. some of our spells may not hit for alot of DMG but for how they hit and what they cost to cast is more than fair. plus theres nothing like haveing a pet (magical tank) to do your dirty work for ya. this is just my opinion on a mage from erudin yours may vary but a high INT means more mana and more casting when you need it.<BR>
<BR>
happy hunting and good luck. im on the prexus server if you have questions.<BR>
Raccan (lords of apocalypse) 17lvl magician
